<subSubSection pageId="17" pageNumber="220" type="discussion">
<paragraph blockId="17.[151,1437,151,791]" pageId="17" pageNumber="220">
<emphasis bold="true" box="[199,328,622,647]" pageId="17" pageNumber="220">Comments</emphasis>
. The species is characterized by the dark body colour, the large body size, the long flagellomeres and the bulbous gonostylus, strongly pointed to the apex, with 4 apical spines. It is similar to 
<taxonomicName authority="Vilkamaa, Hippa &amp; Mohrig" authorityName="Vilkamaa, Hippa &amp; Mohrig" authorityYear="2012" class="Insecta" family="Sciaridae" genus="Bradysia" higherTaxonomySource="GBIF" kingdom="Animalia" order="Diptera" pageId="17" pageNumber="220" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="gibbosa">
<emphasis box="[1195,1315,659,683]" italics="true" pageId="17" pageNumber="220">B. gibbosa</emphasis>
Vilkamaa, Hippa &amp; Mohrig
</taxonomicName>
in the shape of the gonostylus. It differs by the larger body size, the dark colour and the gonostylus with 4 apical spines.
</paragraph>
</subSubSection>
